{
  "stem": "2684.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "In the Saturdays, Sundays, we went to the football match.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And-- and up till 1940, '41, '42, we didn't know much about the war, because Hungary, it seems, was spared of-- of the misery of-- of the war.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "When-- my first knowledge in school was that they called me a Jew-- not even bloody Jew, just Jew.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "But I could whack him in the nose, because nobody ask me why.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "Or when we had a fight, I was the Englishman, they were the Germans, and-- and we lived happily ever after.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "So-- but till 19-- 1944, March, when the Germans came in, that's when the-- the persecution started, in my eyes, as a young boy.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The Jewish community meant that most of my parents' friends were also down from the business side, and about 80% of them were Jews.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We all attended to what we call the-- the [NON-ENGLISH] Synagogue.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That's where I got bar mitzvah.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And-- but we were not a tremendously religious Jews.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And our religious upbringing was that the parents were in the synagogue, and we played soccer in the background-- in the back garden of the-- of the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And my father kept a friendship with a lot of non-Jews.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And-- and that's-- that's about I can say about our Jewish upbringing.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We were very God-fearing.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "My parents, I don't think I ever-- ever heard a rude word said in front of me, since I can remember.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they've been very decent, hardworking people.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And that was our [LAUGHS] contribution to God.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Try not to-- not to take advantage of other people.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Just live and let live.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And that-- that made our [LAUGHS] Jewish conscience clean or clear.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Just Hungarian.",
      "word_count": 2
    }
  ],
